The paper deals with information extraction from visually rich documents, which involves both text and visual information. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of graph convolutional networks suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the task of information extraction is related to information retrieval (cs.IR), which is another possible sub-category.
